misconceptions.inferred_category_name: No misconception detected (correct in-place right rotation)
misconceptions.student_thought_process: The student believes shifting right by one can be done in-place by saving the last element, moving elements right-to-left to avoid overwriting, then writing the saved last element into index 0.
misconceptions.conceptual_gap: No conceptual gap detected. This matches Java’s array semantics (arrays are mutable; assignments overwrite elements immediately), and the right-to-left loop correctly prevents overwriting values that are still needed.
misconceptions.error_manifestation: None; produces correct shifted output for N>=2 and behaves reasonably for N=0 or N=1 (no change).
